# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local environment file — copy this to ".env" (git-ignored).
#
# ".env" holds SECRETS and any per-machine overrides. Non-secret configuration
# defaults live in the committed ".env.defaults" and are documented there; copy
# any of those keys here to override them locally.
#
# In Codespaces/CI these come from the real environment instead, so a missing
# package or file is not an error. On Streamlit Community Cloud, paste secrets
# into the Secrets console (see ".streamlit/secrets.toml.example").
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Secrets: optional cloud embedding/chat providers (Steps 2-5) ─────────────
# Leave every value blank to use the offline default embedding + echo chat
# model, which needs no credentials.

# Amazon Bedrock — Titan embeddings (amazon.titan-embed-text-v2:0) + Claude/Nova chat
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=

# OpenAI — embeddings + chat
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# ── Optional anti-bot escalation for Step 1 crawling (all optional) ──────────
# Comma-separated proxy URLs tried in order (direct first) when a site blocks the
# crawler. Used ONLY on retry rounds (not the initial crawl) to save cost, since
# proxies are a paid service. Residential proxies are usually required to get past
# hard 403s such as Akamai; data-center proxies are often blocked too. Credentials
# may be embedded (e.g. http://user:pass@host:port) and are never logged.
CRAWL_PROXIES=
# Last-resort scraping API: when every browser + proxy attempt is still blocked,
# the crawler GETs this endpoint with `?url=<page>` and uses the returned HTML.
# URL: the API's fetch endpoint from a hosted scraper (e.g. ScraperAPI, ScrapingBee,
#   ZenRows, Bright Data Web Unlocker) — sign up to obtain it; leave blank to disable.
# TOKEN: optional Bearer key sent as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` (omit if the
#   provider authenticates via the URL). Set both only if you have such a provider.
CRAWL_FALLBACK_API_URL=
CRAWL_FALLBACK_API_TOKEN=

# ── Optional non-secret overrides (defaults live in .env.defaults) ───────────
# Uncomment to override a default on this machine, e.g.:
# RAG_TOP_K=6
# VECTOR_CHUNK_SIZE=800
